.TH "spum_create_request" 9 "spum_create_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
spum_create_request \- Build a SPU request message header, up to and including the BD header. Construct the message starting at spu_hdr. Caller should allocate this buffer in DMA-able memory at least SPU_HEADER_ALLOC_LEN bytes long.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" spum_create_request
.BI "(u8 *spu_hdr "  ","
.BI "struct spu_request_opts *req_opts "  ","
.BI "struct spu_cipher_parms *cipher_parms "  ","
.BI "struct spu_hash_parms *hash_parms "  ","
.BI "struct spu_aead_parms *aead_parms "  ","
.BI "unsigned int data_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "spu_hdr" 12
Start of buffer where SPU request header is to be written
.IP "req_opts" 12
SPU request message options
.IP "cipher_parms" 12
Parameters related to cipher algorithm
.IP "hash_parms" 12
Parameters related to hash algorithm
.IP "aead_parms" 12
Parameters related to AEAD operation
.IP "data_size" 12
Length of data to be encrypted or authenticated. If AEAD, does
not include length of AAD.
.SH "RETURN"
the length of the SPU header in bytes. 0 if an error occurs.
